President Donald J. Trump has transmitted a report on the United States Strategy to Defeat the Islamic State of Iraq and Syria (ISIS) to the Congress, along with an analysis of the budgetary resources required for its implementation. This report was previously provided to the Congress on June 23, 2017. Additionally, a report on the legal and policy frameworks guiding the United States' use of military force and related national security operations has also been transmitted. This report was previously provided on March 12, 2018.